text: for a great breakfast or as a delicious
snack try this seated savory quick bread
it comes together in no time at all
because there's no kneading required no
yeast used in the recipe it just all
comes together in one bowl and it's full
of great ingredients like whole wheat
flour spelt flour and a whole array of
seeds that add great texture and flavor
so to get started I have 2 cups of whole
wheat flour in a bowl
I'm going to add to that 2 cups of spelt
flour now both of these flowers are
really nutty wholesome and delicious in
this bread to that I'm going to add my
seeds I have 1/2 a cup of sunflower
seeds 1/2 a cup of black sesame seeds 2
tablespoons caraway seeds now these have
such a great kind of subtle anise flavor
that are really going to be the
predominant flavor of the bread and then
2 tablespoons of flax seed which are
great for digestion 2 teaspoons of a
coarse salt and then this is our leaven
or no yeast but we do need leavener so
we have 2 teaspoons of baking powder and
1 teaspoon of baking soda just going to
whisk these together this is as simple
as making a banana bread very easy now
for the wet ingredients bring this big
bowl over so I need one and a half cups
of whole milk three quarter cup of
buttermilk and it's best if these are at
room temperature that way they'll come
together easily in the bread and will
rise beautifully in the oven okay and
then for a little sweetness two
tablespoons of honey that's it that's
everything in the bread so to this I'm
going add all the dry ingredients just
at once
everybody's in so once it looks like a
batter and there really isn't any visual
signs of dry ingredients we just want to
mix it for about one more minute just to
kind of develop the gluten and increase
the structure of the bread could also do
this on a mixer but it's very easy by
hand and look at all those great seeds
in this batter okay batters all together
so now I'm going to prepare my pan I
have a 9 by 5 inch loaf pan that I have
sprayed and lined with parchment it's
good to leave these overhangs so you can
easily pull the bread out later so I'm
just going to fold the sides down and
then just put this batter right into the
loaf this is the world's easiest bread
okay
that's everything I'm going to even it
out just push it down into the pan get
it nice and level and then I've reserved
some seeds for the top so the top will
have this great domed look with lots of
seeds over the top so I have two
teaspoons of sunflower seeds and I've
toasted these just for an extra little
nuttiness one teaspoon black sesame
seeds these give a great look a great
crunch to this bread a teaspoon of the
caraway seeds very fragrant and a
teaspoon of the flax and these are
golden flax seeds you could also use
brown I like the contrast of the gold
with the rest of the seeds in this bread
so this will go into a 350 degree oven
you want to bake it until a skewer
inserted comes out clean it'll be nice
and domed very very dark golden on top
which is perfect about an hour and five
minutes
okay so the bread cooled for about 20
minutes in the pan and then I've let it
cool completely on this rack and this
bread is amazing it will last for a week
at room temperature well wrapped you can
also freeze it and then slice it and
toast it up it's delicious
I love it just sliced with some butter
and jam or as a snack with some coconut
oil and sliced avocado it's delicious
it's just packed full of seeds and
flavor as very hearty you can see all
those beautiful seeds in there
definitely do this on a cutting board
because the seeds do tend to fly around
but you can eat it just like this you
could toast it up I love it with some
butter on it put some strawberry jam
with the taste of the caraway seeds it's
really nice try this seated savory quick
bread is the answer to homemade bread in
no time at all
